                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hikaru? &gt;&lt;
<br />

<br />
Theres actually quite a bit of sites to use to buy parts.  I've only used newegg.com and tigerdirect.com so I am unable to reffer any others. They have been great to deal with and cheap without any hassles.
<br />

<br />
WinXP does not support AMD 64's as far as I know (I've heard a rumor of a WinXP 64Bit Beta thats available for download but I don't know since I don't use windows)
<br />
Pentium 4 HT's act as a second CPU and are compatible with WinXP, don't know what kind of performance you'd get with WinXP though.
<br />

<br />
My suggestions though, if <span style="font-weight: bold">I</span> was going to build a new computer, I would definitely go with the AMD64, get a GeForce 5700 or 6600, about 2 gigs of memory, probably at 533MHz using S-ATA Raid.
<br />

<br />
Don't really know what you want, I believe when I bought my computer, I paid 1400USD for the box alone I believe off tigerdirect and newegg, it has:
<br />
Asus P4P800-E Deluxe (800MHz FSB) with P4 2.8GHz HT
<br />
XFx 5600FX 256MB
<br />
2-120GB EIDE HD's ATA-100's
<br />
Sony DVD+/-RW, was one of the best at the time, don't know at present
<br />
2-512MB 400MHz Memory Sticks
<br />

<br />
I also purchased a Logitech z680 Speaker system, its 5.1 surround at 450W RMS and a Creative Labs Sound Blaster Audigy 2 card, can't really remeber the prices completely, but I believe it the overall total I paid was something like 2k  but I bought a $200dvd burner, $200 surround?, the monitor also included in total price was like $400 as well as a few other goodies.
<br />

<br />
Don't know what to tell you other than, newegg is pretty nice since it offers customer feedback.
<br />
Check this site also, even though its linux compatibility related talk, its good to use to get feedback on parts.
<br />
<a href="http://www.linuxquestions.org/hcl/index.php" target="_blank">http://www.linuxquestions.org/hcl/index.php</a></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
