                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><a href="http://www.zipzoomfly.com" target="_blank">www.zipzoomfly.com</a> &lt;formerly known as Googlegear.com&gt; is one of the better.  Pricewatch is a good site, but make sure you check sources before purchasing, and be aware of low priced items with HIGH priced shipping charges.  
<br />
As for Hardware suggestions I highly recommend checking out MaximumPC.com  I have been building machines for about 8 years now and have found Maximum to be on the money and up to date on nearly any hardware question or problem you can come up with.  
<br />

<br />
My #1 maxim to building a new machine is to buy the biggest baddest Motherboard you can find, don't skimp on the price at all.  If you need to scale back, do it elsewhere.  You can always upgrade smaller pieces when funding becomes available, but your Motherboard will limit all your future upgrading abilities if you don't purchase well.
<br />

<br />
