                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">IMO a gaming system takes a 300$ video card every 2 years as much RAM as you can find and little else.  Edit: But if your going to stick with just WoW then Get the best Video Card you can right now and then wait till they upgrade the game's graphics to upgrade the card.
<br />

<br />
If your going for a 1500$ system I would grab a geforce 6800 GT @ 390$ and a 64bit AMD CPU there 30% faster clock for clock than 32 bit CPU 's even on 32 bit apps. So an AMD Athlon 64 2800+ @ 141$  is worth a  Athlon 32bit running at 3640.  If you going to store a lot of stuff on it go for 3 200gig HDD in a raid 5 for 300$.  You end up with 400Gigs of HDD that’s FAST and if one drive fails your still fine.  But a single 200gig drive is huge for a pure gaming box.
<br />

<br />
Get a good Main / mother board with integrated sound and LAN. (I have a high end sound card and I don’t use it as it’s not worth the waste heat into my case.)  I like Abit but it’s up to you.
<br />

<br />
Get a DVD burner there cheep new egg has a Lite-On 8x DVD drive for 65$ so there is little point in not getting one.  You may want to grab a 2nd DVD drive for disk to disk copy's up to you.
<br />

<br />
Hmm, Looking at newegg.com I come up with.
<br />
Giga-byte nVIDIA GeForce 6800 GT Video Card, 256MB GDDR3, 256-Bit @ 399$
<br />
AMD Athlon 64 2800+- Retail @ 141$ 
<br />
Some Socket 754 mother Board @ 130$ I like Abit but it’s up to you.
<br />
Three Seagate 200GB 7200RPM IDE Hard @ 324$
<br />
Lite-On 8x DVD drive @ 65$
<br />
Microsoft Windows XP HOME -OEM (I use XP pro but Home works fine)@ 91$
<br />
Case 130$ you want a 400+W powersuply if your using 3 HDD and a high end VidoCard.
<br />
Two Crucial 184 Pin 512MB DDR PC-3200 @ 190$  (You could go for faster but I wanted to keep the price down a little there at the end.)
<br />

<br />
Total 1470$ you could drop that down to 1184 with one HDD and a low end case (60$) if you where going to get a monitor or needed some extra's like a keyboard / mouse and some speakers.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
