                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I kind of doubt the cost effectiveness of SLI.  You're already going to be paying a $100 premium just for the motherboard that supports it, which is probably at least what a Geforce 6600 GT will cost in a year, to make $200 extra.  With that $200 on top of the $200 for a 6600GT currently, you could simply buy a 6800GT which will generally perform better than 2 6600GTs and you'll have that performance right now.  I don't see any reason for Nvidia's SLI to be more successful than 3dfx's with the Voodoo 2.
<br />

<br />
I think PCI Express is only useful if you plan to replace your video card before replacing your motherboard since it offers little if any performance increase over a comparable AGP setup.  I have never done that except when I got my first 3D accelerator ever, yes, a Voodoo2, and no, I never bought a second one for SLI.  If the AGP and PCI Express systems are the same price, obviously go for the latter, but I wouldn't personally pay a premium of $100 or more just to have it, and I'm not sure exactly how the prices are working out.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
