                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I would like to pick up on where Hikaru had mentioned monitors.
<br />

<br />
The most important part aside from a working system getting done what it needs to be getting done is what you interface yourself with.
<br />

<br />
You need a keyboard that isn't a piece of shit, same with the mouse, but the monitor is the most important part of your computer.
<br />

<br />
People will talk all day about this CPU, or that graphics card over there, or this huge amount of RAM, etc.  And yet most usually a monitor never ends up in the conversation and it's really the most important part.
<br />

<br />
Also your monitor retains more value over time than anything else.  Sure its obsolete from day one like any other computer component, however it retains value considerably longer than other components.
<br />

<br />
If you have to skimp on something, skimp all you have to as long as you end up with the most badass monitor you can aquire.  The monitor will usually last a LOT longer than anything else, typically up into the 3 systems later range.  (well, from my experiences, anyway)
<br />

<br />
I did myself a favor last year and bought a Nokia 445xPro 21" monitor.  I'm an innate NEC monitor fan but I couldn't quit reading good things about this monitor in particular, so I took a plunge.
<br />

<br />
I think all said and done I paid $279 or so (including shipping).  Got it off eBay.  When it arrived apparently it had came off a corporate lease or something because I couldn't even find a single scratch on it, it even had the "new" smell and I checked the date when it was manufactured and found it was made in late 1998.  Your mileage may vary naturally.
<br />

<br />
As far as CRT's go the bloody thing is like looking at crystal.  It helps I use BNC monitor cables instead of the general D-Sub connector, but even when in D-Sub mode it ain't too shabby neither.
<br />

<br />
Point is, this old 1998 model monitor can seriously stand up to stuff being manufactured and sold in 2004.  Last time I was at Micro Center or any other computer store they didn't even sell anything that was an improvement.
<br />

<br />
Invest in a nice monitor, do yourself a favor, everything else is a bonus.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Bedazzler & Forest Stalker, Vadeanya & Zardak Zepiroth.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
