                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I agree. A decent monitor is a great investment. I have a 21" trinitron as my main media viewing and gaming monitor and a 19" LCD as a work monitor and for web browsing. This is a dual screen setup which means the monitors act as an extension of one large desktop with the mouse jumping between them when I move them off screen. I have had my 21" trinitron monitor through numorous upgrades over the years. I've changed maybe 2500+ dollars in parts in the last 4 years and have kept the 21" monitor and only last year bought the 19" LCD. A good monitor is indeed an overlooked part of a good computer system. A cheezy bad monitor can produce fuzzy text onscreen (I've seen it happen) and that can cause eye strain. One thing an LCD is great at is producing crisp text.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-style: italic">On the other hand, if your reaction to something I say boils down to "You didn't choose MY side, make MY choice," well, you're not looking for information, you're looking for someone to tell you how smart you are thinking the way you do. --</span> <span style="font-weight: bold">Ed Stroligo</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
